# Data Processing Agreement (Template)

_Generated by SKILL-ASTRO (W8 #282). Review with legal before executing._

This Data Processing Agreement ("DPA") is entered into between the
Customer (Controller) and **{{ project_name }}** operator (Processor).

## Subject-matter

Processor will process personal data solely to provide the services
described in the primary service agreement.

## Categories of data subjects

End users of the Customer's instance, administrative accounts used
by the Customer's staff, and content editors operating the headless
CMS where applicable.

## Categories of personal data

Identifiers (email, account ID), authentication metadata, usage logs,
and any content the Customer uploads.

## Sub-processors

A current list is published at `/legal/sub-processors`. If the
`cms` knob is `sanity` or `contentful`, the chosen CMS provider is
listed as a sub-processor. Customer is notified of any additions
with 30 days' lead time.

## Security measures

See `docs/privacy/security.md` — ISO 27001-aligned controls.

## Data subject rights

Processor assists Controller with right-to-access, erasure, and
portability requests via `/api/privacy/*` endpoints.
